Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 77/98 of 9 January 1998 on certain procedures for applying the Cooperation Agreement between the European Community and the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia (1), and in particular Article 3(1) thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EC) No 273/98 of 2 February 1998 opening and providing for the administration of Community tariff quotas and tariff ceilings and establishing a Community surveillance of reference quantities for certain products originating in the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia (2), provides in its Article 2 an exemption from customs duties in the framework of tariff ceilings for the products listed in its Annex B;
Whereas Article 3(1) of Regulation (EC) No 77/98 provides that the Commission may, as soon as a tariff ceiling is reached, adopt a Regulation reintroducing, until the end of the calendar year, the customs duties applicable to third countries in respect of imports of the products concerned; whereas the Community surveillance provided by Article 2(3) of Regulation (EC) No 273/98 has shown that preferential imports of products in the framework of the tariff ceiling with order No 25.0230 have exceeded this ceiling;
Whereas this situation is liable to cause serious damage to the Community sector concerned and requires the reintroduction of customs duties;
Whereas the levying of customs duties for these products should therefore be re-established,
